<title>USA: Dillard Department Stores Q4 net, shr rise.</title>
<headline>Dillard Department Stores Q4 net, shr rise.</headline>
<dateline>LITTLE ROCK, Ark 1997-02-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>1997			1996</p>
<p> Shr		 $0.98		    $0.26</p>
<p> Net		 111,100		  29,100</p>
<p> Sales	     1,937,400		1,920,600</p>
<p> Avg shrs	  113,800		  113,200</p>
<p>	  12 MONTHS</p>
<p> Shr		 $2.09		    $1.48</p>
<p> Net		 238,600		  167,200</p>
<p> Sales	     6,227,600		5,918,000</p>
<p> Avg shrs	  114,000		  113,100</p>
<p>(All data above 000s except per share numbers)</p>
<p>NOTES: Earnings for Q4 and full year 1995 included a non-cash after-tax charge of $78.5 million, or $0.69 per share, from early adoption of Statement of Financial Accounting Standards No. 121 regarding impairment of long-lived assets.</p>
<p>Sales for Q4 ended Feb. 1, 1997, were $1.94 billion, and sales on a comparable 13-week basis for the year-ago quarter were $1.84 billion.</p>
<p>Full company name is Dillard Department Stores Inc.</p>
